'''César Jair Samudio Murillo''' (born 23 February 1994) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Honduran side [[C.D. Marathón|Marathón]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Panama City]], Samudio played as a senior for [[Chepo F.C.|Chepo]], [[Atlético Veragüense]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://jmdeportes.com/futbol/futbol-nacional/lpf/veraguense-ficha-a-jugador-de-la-seleccion/|title=Veragüense ficha a jugador de la selección|trans-title=Veragüense sign a player from the national team|publisher=JM Deportes|language=es|date=11 July 2016|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref> [[Club Deportivo del Este|Costa del Este]], [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]] and [[C.A. Independiente de La Chorrera|CAI]] in his home country. He won the [[2022 Liga Panameña de Fútbol]] with the latter, being named the Most Valuable Player of the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvn-2.com/tvmax/somos-la-sele/panama-cesar-samudio-galardonado-gala_1_2025042.html|title=Panamá: César Samudio, el más galardonado en gala del fútbol panameño 2022|trans-title=Panama: César Samudio, the most awarded at the 2022 Panamanian football gala|publisher=[[TVN (Panamanian TV network)|TVN]]|language=es|date=14 December 2022|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref>

On 7 January 2023, Samudio moved abroad and signed for [[C.D. Marathón|Marathón]] in Honduras.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/cesar-samudio-mvp-la-lpf-ficha-el-cd-marathon-n5828005|title=César Samudio (MVP de la LPF) ficha por el CD Marathón|trans-title=César Samudio (LPF's MVP) signs for CD Marathón|publisher=[[RPC Televisión]]|language=es|date=7 January 2023|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref> Initially on loan, he signed a permanent contract until December 2026 with the club on 26 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/el-cd-marathon-adquiere-ficha-completa-del-panameno-cesar-samudio-n5885245|title=El CD Marathón adquiere ficha completa del panameño César Samudio|trans-title=CD Marathón purchase the full rights of Panamanian César Samudio|publisher=[[RPC Televisión]]|language=es|date=26 May 2023|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Samudio received his first call-up to the [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in April 2022, for a non-[[FIFA]] [[Exhibition match|friendly]] against [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/marea-roja/cesar-samudio-se-respeta-lo-que-decida-cada-club-porque-no-es-fecha-fifa-n5700299|title=César Samudio: "Se respeta lo que decida cada club, porque no es fecha FIFA"|trans-title=César Samudio: "We respect what each club say, because it is not a FIFA date"|publisher=[[RPC Televisión]]|language=es|date=28 April 2022|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref> He made his debut on 1 May, starting in the 3–2 loss at the [[WakeMed Soccer Park]] in [[Cary, North Carolina]].

Samudio's full international debut occurred on 10 June 2023, replacing [[Luis Mejía]] in a 3–2 win over [[Nicaragua national football team|Nicaragua]].

